This code is taken from https://medium.com/swlh/install-puppet-server-on-docker-fe4a80cbe3be

To run the dockerized puppet infrastructure, run 'DNS_ALT_NAMES=host.exam docker-compose up -d'. For more details, go to the above link.

We are following puppet tutorial from this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PL_J5Gj3GAQ

Towards the end of this tutorial, the mysqld service didn't start because these docker containers don't have systemd which is needed by mysqld. So, I've left the module at that.